  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Prevention of the Spread of Ebola in Sierra Leone, Guinea and Liberia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 251 communities in operational areas in Sierra Leone and Liberia, this project will carry out health education and information sharing, hold emergency coordination and planning meetings at the operational level, and develop and implement monitoring.

ChildFund will concentrate on non-medical interventions, working with government and health-related NGOs through its local partners, to raise awareness in the affected communities to reduce the risks of the spread of Ebola. ChildFund, in collaboration with the relevant government line ministries and the Child Protection Cluster, will develop and adapt Ebola IEC materials and produce them for distribution in the 251 affected communities. ChildFund will train community mobilizers, community health workers and parent volunteers to conduct community awareness and sensitization sessions and support them with the necessary instruments, such as megaphones and batteries, to share the messages in the communities. The project has worked with local FM radio stations to organize radio discussions on Ebola. The project has also provided communities with hygiene and sanitation kits for use in public places and at home.</narrative>
  </description>
